ng as the URL is the HTTPS endpoint for the ClickHouse HTTP interface."},"77":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-32","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"Use the connection details from the ClickHouse Cloud service connection menu. For the Node.js or HTTPS connection form, the URL usually has this shape:"},"78":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-33","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"Then configure the ingest service the same way you would for a self-hosted production deployment:"},"79":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-34","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"Run migrations from a trusted environment that can reach the ClickHouse Cloud service:"},"80":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-35","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"The browser SDK and React package do not connect to ClickHouse Cloud directly. They should continue to send events to the ingest service `apiHost`; the ingest service is the only component that needs ClickHouse Cloud credentials."},"81":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-36","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Variable"},"82":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-37","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Required"},"83":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-38","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Default"},"84":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-39","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployme